column60: Green is often the colour used to symbolize the environment. Green also societally means “Go” or “Good” (whereas red may tend to symbolize “Stop” or “Danger). I think this stems back from when humans were primitive and most of the things we saw in the forest was green so it was a safe colour but red was a less familiar colour. Also sustainable brands tend to have already adopted green as a symbol colour so maybe our brains just start to expect that association. As I am more active with environmental activism I am more inclined to look at specific labels on the packaging.
